      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DISTANT SUN (3) looks close to a win after seconds in two of three starts so far this campaign, the latest at Melton behind an in-form rival. Switches to a standing start but should be nearing peak fitness now. RUN FOREST RUN NZ (4) has been competitive of late, placing in both starts since a Birchip win. Kept the ball rolling last time when he came from the back row to be 4 metres into second at Kilmore. Leading hope. OUR MARVELLA NZ (8) led and faded in the Geelong Cup four weeks ago but had placed in the Ararat and Goulburn cups prior so is worth another chance. SEBASTIANS BOY (9) is building in fitness. Drops in grade and will relish the return to a circuit and distance where he has won three of four attempts.",
